I'm trying to use a simple macro in a single template stream but I don't seem to be able to execute the macro.

Here is a test that I would expect to work

{code}
[Test]
public void MacroTest()
{
    var velocity = new VelocityEngine();
    var props = new ExtendedProperties();
    velocity.Init(props);
    var context = new VelocityContext();
    context.Put("foo", "ItWorks");
    var writer = new StringWriter();
    var template = @"#macro( callme $a )
$a $a $a
#end

#callme( $foo )";
    velocity.Evaluate(context, writer, null, template);
    Assert.That(writer.ToString(), Is.Not.StringContaining("#callme( ItWorks )"));
    Assert.That(writer.ToString(), Is.StringContaining("ItWorks ItWorks ItWorks"));
}
{code}

Am I missing something? or is this a valid bug. I have looked around and I can't seem to find any examples that work for me.
